    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Animals belonging to species that are not domesticated and have not been altered by humans through selective breeding to modify behavior or appearance; includes wild species of animals that are cared for by humans in a zoo, park or other place, even if the animal has been bred and raised in captivity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>未經馴養以及未經人工篩選育種，以改變其行為或外觀的動物；包括在動物園、公園或其他場所受人照料的野生物種，即使被關在籠中由人培育與飼養，仍屬於野生動物。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dieren behorend tot soorten die niet gedomesticeerd zijn en niet door middel van selectief fokken door de mens zijn veranderd om hun gedrag of uiterlijk aan te passen; inclusief wilde diersoorten die door mensen worden verzorgd in een dierentuin of -park of elders, zelfs als het dier in gevangenschap is geboren en opgegroeid.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
